data.message: Witness the crowds of pilgrims walk together from Mendut temple to Borobodur carrying the flame of eternal fire as one of the rituals during the holy Vesak Day on 9th May 2017. The eternal flames are taken from Mrapen in the Grobogan village, Purwodadi district, Central Java. Along with the holy water and Buddhist symbols, the flame is carefully guarded in the Mendut temple to be paraded and used during the ceremony at Borobudur on Vesak day. #WoderfulIndonesia

data.description: Dieng Plateau has a million dazzling beauties, with an extraordinary natural and cultural wealth. In this region, in addition to shady green trees and beautifully patterned Hindu temples, here is also a beautiful natural gift called Telaga Warna, (the Colorful Lake), an icon of this area.
data.message: Approximately 25 miles’ drive from Wonosobo, the Dieng Plateau is rich in natural and cultural wealth. While in Dieng, make sure you visit Telaga Warna (The Colorful Lake) and witness its mystical beauty. The high sulphuric content in the lake causes the water to change in fluctuating colors of green, yellow, purple and even rainbow hues. #WonderfulIndonesia

data.description: Jakarta has no less than 140 Chinese temples across this sprawling cosmopolitan city. However, oldest among them all is the temple at Petak Sembilan in Jakarta’s Chinatown, locally better known as Glodok.
data.message:
Jakarta has a plethora of Chinese temples, yet the oldest and most attractive one is the Jin De Yuan or Vihara Dharma Bhakti temple in the capital’s Petak Sembilan area. The temple is dedicated to the goddess Kwan Im and covers 3,000 square meters. During the first and 15th day of the new moon, devotees come to the temple to burn incense or light candles in honor of the goddess and ask the Almighty for protection and prosperity. #WonderfulIndonesia

Photo by Gunawan Kartapranata
data.name: Vihara Dharma Bhakti (The Jin De Yuan)
